bilingual.source: Cell passage is an important step in cell culture.
bilingual.target: 细胞传代是细胞培养中的一个重要步骤。

bilingual.source: The cell membrane controls what enters and leaves the cell.
bilingual.target: 细胞膜控制进入和离开细胞的物质。

bilingual.source: Proteins on the cell membrane help in cell communication.
bilingual.target: 细胞膜上的蛋白质有助于细胞间的交流。

bilingual.source: A karyocyte is a cell that has a nucleus.
bilingual.target: 有核细胞是指具有细胞核的细胞。

bilingual.source: Glycolysis occurs in the cytoplasm of the cell.
bilingual.target: 糖酵解发生在细胞的细胞质中。

bilingual.source: Killer cell can attack and destroy cancer cells.
bilingual.target: 杀伤细胞可以攻击并摧毁癌细胞。

bilingual.source: Apoptosis is a natural process of cell death.
bilingual.target: 细胞凋亡是细胞死亡的一种自然过程。

bilingual.source: Proteins are synthesized in the cytoplasm of the cell.
bilingual.target: 蛋白质在细胞的细胞质中合成。

bilingual.source: Scientists use fcs to analyze cell populations.
bilingual.target: 科学家们使用流式细胞术来分析细胞群体。

bilingual.source: The cytoskeleton provides structural support for the cell.
bilingual.target: 细胞骨架为细胞提供结构支撑。

list.abstract: CELL（英 [sel]，美 [sel]），英语单词，名词，意思为单人牢房；细胞；电解电池。短语搭配有cancer cell（癌细胞）。例句为“Many small living things with one cell live there.（许多单细胞的小生物生活在那里。）” CELL相关近义词有electric battery、electric element。

《CELL》（《细胞》）是一种美国爱思维尔(Elsevier)出版公司旗下的细胞出版社(Cell Press)发行的关于生命科学领域最新研究发现的杂志。 2018年1月25日，克隆猴“中中”和“华华”登上学术期刊《细胞》封面，这意味着中国科学家成功突破了现有技术无法克隆灵长类动物的世界难题。2018年9月，世界顶尖科学期刊《Cell》发表文章称，新的两项研究表明，服用益生菌不仅没有好处，还可能对人体有害。2019年，Cancer Cell最新刊登了一篇文章，研究人员发现在禁食状态下使用二甲双胍可以显著抑制肿瘤生长，并提出PP2A-GSK3β-MCL-1通路可能是肿瘤治疗的新靶点。

yingyinNormal.en: Animal and plant cells have cell membranes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 动物细胞和植物细胞都有细胞膜。

yingyinNormal.en: Just like any simple cell going through time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就像任何细胞随着时间老化。

yingyinNormal.en: The cell membrane is covered with tiny projections.
yingyinNormal.zh: 细胞膜上有很多突出的部分。

yingyinNormal.en: Some regulate the cell cycle more effectively than others.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它们中的某些在调节细胞周期上比其他要更高效。

yingyinNormal.en: Normally, cell division follows an orderly process called the cell cycle, which is basically the life cycle of a cell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一般来说，细胞分裂遵循一个叫做“细胞周期”的有序的进程，也就是一个细胞的生命周期。

yingyinNormal.en: Pretending to be a friend, it attaches to a projection on the cell membrane, and the cell brings it through the cell membrane and inside.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它假装是一个朋友，连到细胞膜上的一个突出部分，然后细胞让它穿过细胞膜进来。

yingyinNormal.en: They then send one of the pieces back through the cell membrane, where the cell displays it to warn neighboring cells about the invader.
yingyinNormal.zh: 之后它们把其中的一块放到细胞膜外面，这样细胞就可以警示它旁边的细胞：有入侵者。

yingyinNormal.en: Electrical impulses. Every cell knows and talks to every other cell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 电脉冲，每个细胞都懂得互相沟通。

yingyinNormal.en: Each cell in your body is surrounded by a cell membrane, a thick flexible layer made of fats and proteins, that surrounds and protects the inner components.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你身体里的每一个细胞都是被细胞膜所包起来。那是由脂肪和蛋白质组成的一层即厚又软的物质，包围着并保护着细胞内部。

yingyinNormal.en: They all have functions, like helping cells adhere to their neighbors or binding to nutrients the cell will need.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它们都有用处的，比如帮助细胞吸附住临近的细胞，或帮细胞链接上营养物质。

yingyinNormal.en: Within the cell cycle is a series of checkpoints, where proteins, such as the one produced by BRCA1, regulate how fast the cell may proceed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在细胞周期内有一系列的检验点，是诸如由乳腺癌1号基因制造的蛋白质调节细胞分裂速度的地方。

yingyinNormal.en: Enclosed in a bubble made of the same material as the cell membrane, the golgi apparatus also gives the antibody directions, telling it how to get to the edge of the cell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 包在一个由细胞膜物质组成的泡泡里，高基式体也会给抗体指示，告诉它怎么去细胞的边缘。

yingyinNormal.en: Only plant cells have a cell wall, which is made of rigid cellulose that gives the plant structure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是只有植物细胞有细胞壁，当中坚硬的纤维素给植物制造了他的结构。

yingyinNormal.en: But before it can do that, the antibody needs to leave the cell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但在那之前，抗体必须得离开细胞。

yingyinNormal.en: The cell ejects the antibody, and it heads out to track down the virus.
yingyinNormal.zh: 细胞射出抗体，然后抗体去找那病毒。

yingyinNormal.en: Tumor suppressor genes are involved in regulating how fast a cell divides.
yingyinNormal.zh: 肿瘤抑制基因参与控制细胞分裂速度。

yingyinNormal.en: A nearby cell sees the warning and immediately goes into action.
yingyinNormal.zh: 旁边一个细胞看到了这个警示，立刻开始行动。

yingyinNormal.en: You have two copies of the BRCA1 gene in every cell of your body.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在你身体的每个细胞内，乳腺癌1号基因有两个副本。

yingyinNormal.en: When it gets there, the bubble surrounding the antibody fuses to the cell membrane.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当它到了那里，包着抗体的泡泡融入细胞膜。

yingyinNormal.en: This redundancy is a good thing because you only need one functioning BRCA1 gene in a cell to regulate the cell cycle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这种“多余”其实是件好事，因为你虽然只需要一个乳腺癌1号基因工作就能控制细胞周期。

examination_example.sentence: A animal brain is more than "a mass of <highlight>cells</highlight> that communicate by electricity" .
examination_example.sentence_trans: 动物大脑不仅仅只是“大量的细胞通过电流进行交流”。

examination_example.sentence: Some scientists have argued that plants possess neuron-like <highlight>cells</highlight> that interact with hormones and neurotransmitters.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些科学家认为，植物拥有与激素和神经递质相互作用的神经元样细胞。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Cells</highlight> in plants also communicate through electrical signals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 植物中的细胞也通过电信号进行交流。

examination_example.sentence: Statistical errors are alarmingly common in published research, according to David Vaux, a <highlight>cell</highlight> biologist.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 细胞生物学家戴维·沃克斯表示，统计错误在已发表的研究中非常常见。
